        <trans-unit id="123" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Note that the blue component in the fourth color bar went from 0.8 to 0.6.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="124" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>That is because <ph id="ph1">[!INCLUDE[ndptecgdiplus](../../../../includes/ndptecgdiplus-md.md)]</ph> retains only the fractional part of the result.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="125" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, (2)(0.8) = 1.6, and the fractional part of 1.6 is 0.6.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="126" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Retaining only the fractional part ensures that the result is always in the interval [0, 1].</source>
        </trans-unit>
